properties.name: ERpos
properties.ontology_reference: The yes/no indicator for information related to the description or status of estrogen receptors, cytoplasmic hormone-activated receptors that act as nuclear transcription factors composed of an N-terminal transcription activation/modulation domain and a C-terminal steroid-binding domain, based on percentage and intensity of stained cells.

properties.name: PgRpos
properties.ontology_reference: The yes/no indicator for information related to the description or status of progesterone receptors, specific proteins found in or on cells of progesterone target tissues that specifically combine with progesterone, based on percentage and intensity of stained cells.

properties.name: HR Pos
properties.ontology_reference: the last outcome from pathologic tests to determine presence and nature of cancer by evaluating a sample of breast tissue for ligand binding proteins (hormones) present in or produced by tumor.

properties.name: Her2MostPos
properties.ontology_reference: Text term to signify testing was done for the gene that controls cell growth by making the human epidermal growth factor receptor 2, detected by immunohistochemical means.

properties.name: BilateralCa
properties.ontology_reference: the yes/no indicator related to enrollment in research study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes for patient that has bilateral carcinoma arising from the breast, most commonly the terminal ductal-lobular unit.

properties.name: Laterality
properties.ontology_reference: for a tumor in a paired organ, a designation for the side of the body on which the tumor or cancer first developed.

properties.name: MRI LD Baseline
properties.ontology_reference: LD spans all disease present (inv & DCIS) even if there is intervening normal tissue, in mm, at baseline

properties.name: MRI LD 1-3dAC
properties.ontology_reference: LD spans all disease present (inv & DCIS) even if there is intervening normal tissue, in mm, at 1-3days after start of AC

properties.name: MRI LD InterReg
properties.ontology_reference: LD spans all disease present (inv & DCIS) even if there is intervening normal tissue, in mm, at Inter-regimen

properties.name: MRI LD PreSurg
properties.ontology_reference: LD spans all disease present (inv & DCIS) even if there is intervening normal tissue, in mm, at Pre-surgery
